post_text: After careful consideration PCS will be closed 1/30/19 due to the extreme wind chill warning issued by the National Weather Service. Although we no longer have buses, there are still concerns with the number of students and staff who walk/use public transportation along with the traveling between buildings for classes and lunches. We hope being able to make the call ahead of time will help you avoid the dreaded morning scramble. Stay safe and bundled up if you have to go out.

post_text: After careful consideration unfortunately PCS will be closed tomorrow 1-16-18 due to the extreme wind chill advisory in effect through early afternoon. Although we no longer have buses, we are concerned with the large number of students who walk/use public transportation along with the constant walking from building to building that takes place throughout the day. We realize this makes it difficult for many families which is why we are making the call this evening and not waiting until the morning hoping this will help with the morning scramble. This is always a tough decision and we appreciate your continued partnership. If you have to go out make sure to bundle up.
